ArcelorMittal May Bid for Raspadskaya, Vedomosti Reports

-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-04-11T08:57:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/arcelormittal-may-bid-for-russia-s-raspadskaya-vedomosti-says.html
ArcelorMittal (MT) , the world’s largest
steelmaker, may bid for the 80 percent of Russian coal producer
OAO Raspadskaya that’s being sold by shareholders,  Vedomosti
reported , citing people it didn't identify.  Russia’s OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  and Ukraine’s MetInvest may also bid,
the Moscow-based newspaper said.  Giles Read, a spokesman for ArcelorMittal in London, said
the steelmaker doesn’t comment on speculation, while Raspadskaya
spokesman Alexander Andreev declined to comment. Mechel
spokeswoman Ekarerina Videman also didn’t want to comment.  Evraz Group SA (EVR) , which has a 40 percent stake in Raspadskaya, 
said March 11 it's considering options for its stake. A company
spokesman, who declined to be identified, didn't comment today.   Metinvest spokesman Ivan Shmidik declined to comment,
saying the company is “constantly exploring opportunities”
to expand its business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow on  at
 yfedorinova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
